    <p>
        If You Are Willing To Go To Nagaland And Want To Have A Complete Experience Then Don’t Make Less Than 4 -5 Days Tour.  If You Are Only Interested In Specific Place Like Kohima, Dimapur Etc. Or You Are Interested In Outdoor Activities Like Trekking Then 1-2 Days Tour Is Enough To Enjoy This State.
        </p>
    <p>
        Central Market For Ladies, Waterfalls, Hills And Langpangkong Caves For Nature Lovers, Fakim Sanctuary, Intanki Wildlife Sanctuaryetc. For Wildlife, Dzukou Valley And Tura River For Adventure Or Outdoor Activities Means This State Is The Small Package Of Entertainment And Enjoyment. So It Is Up To You How You Want To Enjoy Here. It Is Promise By Ibg, That You Will Definitely Going To Enjoy Nagaland.
        </p>

    <p>
        The Journey To The Extreme North Eastern Part Of India Is Arduous And Extremely Adventurous In Its Nature. Trekking Through The Challenging Terrains Of Arunachal Pradesh With Outstanding Stock Of Varied Botanical Species Is Purely Unique And Breath-Holding. The Route To Each Trek Is A Quite Unique Experience.
    </p>
   
    
    <p>
        <b>1 – 2 Days Tour :</b> In This Tour Package You Can Do A Lots Of Outdoor Activities. Like Trekking In Dzukou Valley Or Pulie Badze Etc. You Can Also Spent Your Time By Angling In The Rivers Like In Tula River Or Doyang River. Another Best Option Is For You Caving In The Langpangkong Caves, But Try To Avoid Caves If You Are With Kids As Caves Are Dark. You Can Also Visit To Kohima And Enjoy In Local Tourists Places Of Kohima Like War Cemetery, Zoo, Japfu Peak And Other Destinations.
       
    </p>
